3 Methods: Data preprocessing

3.1 Creating ID values for UMCG sample

dataUMCG$ID <- paste0("UMCG", seq(1, nrow(dataUMCG)))

3.2 Pre defined transformation

#change direction; higher scores better perception
dataEMC$TAS20_fac1_tf <- 35 - dataEMC$TAS20_fac1_Identificeren_Gevoelens 
dataUMCG$TAS20_fac1_tf <- 35 - dataUMCG$TAS20_fac1_Identificeren_Gevoelens

3.3 Synchronizing names and compute totals

#adding total scores for FP subset to EMC data
dataEMC$FP_1_6_total <- dataEMC$FP_1t6_ToM + dataEMC$FP_1t6_empathy 

#adding total scores for SET items to UMCG EMC data
dataEMC$SET_UMCG_1 <- dataEMC$SET_open_2 + dataEMC$SET_mc_2
dataEMC$SET_UMCG_2 <- dataEMC$SET_open_3 + dataEMC$SET_mc_3
dataEMC$SET_UMCG_3 <- dataEMC$SET_open_6 + dataEMC$SET_mc_6
dataEMC$SET_UMCG_4 <- dataEMC$SET_open_14 + dataEMC$SET_mc_14
dataEMC$SET_UMCG_5 <- dataEMC$SET_open_16 + dataEMC$SET_mc_16
dataEMC$SET_UMCG_6 <- dataEMC$SET_open_17 + dataEMC$SET_mc_17
dataEMC$SET_UMCG_total <- dataEMC$SET_UMCG_1 + dataEMC$SET_UMCG_2 +dataEMC$SET_UMCG_3 +dataEMC$SET_UMCG_4 +dataEMC$SET_UMCG_5 +dataEMC$SET_UMCG_6

#realising identical column names
colnames(dataUMCG)[which(colnames(dataUMCG) == "SET_UMCG_Totaal")] <- "SET_UMCG_total"

#calculating subscores of SET subset to EMC data
dataEMC$SET_UMCG_Cognitief_Totaal <- dataEMC$SET_UMCG_1 +dataEMC$SET_UMCG_2 + dataEMC$SET_UMCG_3
dataEMC$SET_UMCG_Affectief_Totaal <- dataEMC$SET_UMCG_4 +dataEMC$SET_UMCG_5 + dataEMC$SET_UMCG_6

#full 3 factor model
m1_f3fm <- '
# Defining the factors (latent variables)
f1_P =~ EKM + ERT + TASf1
f2_U =~ SET + FP + CART
f3_R =~ RSMSf1 + SNQ + MBI

# Allow factors to be correlated
f1_P ~~ f2_U
f1_P ~~ f3_R
f2_U ~~ f3_R
'

#two factor model: f1 = f2
m2_2fm_1eq2 <- '
# Defining the factors (latent variables)
f1_P =~ EKM + ERT + TASf1
f2_U =~ SET + FP + CART
f3_R =~ RSMSf1 + SNQ + MBI

# Allow factors to be correlated
f1_P ~~ 1*f2_U  # Fix correlation between f1_P and f2_U at 1
f1_P ~~ r*f3_R
f2_U ~~ r*f3_R
'

#model 3: two factor model: f1 = f3 (CART)
m3_2fm_1eq3 <- '
# Defining the factors (latent variables)
f1_P =~ EKM + ERT + TASf1
f2_U =~ SET + FP + CART
f3_R =~ RSMSf1 + SNQ + MBI

# Allow factors to be correlated
f1_P ~~ r*f2_U  
f1_P ~~ 1*f3_R # Fix correlation between f1_P and f3_R at 1
f2_U ~~ r*f3_R
'

f3_R =~ RSMSf1 + SNQ + MBI

#regression
TQ ~ f1_P + f2_U + f3_R

# Factor structure based on analysis 1: U=BR
f1_P ~~ r*f2_U  
f1_P ~~ r*f3_R 
f2_U ~~ 1*f3_R
